ry%20year%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhat%20is%20my%20debt%20payoff%20date%20%E2%80%94%20the%20exact%20month%20and%20year%20that%20I%20will%20be%20debt-free%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhat%20percentage%20of%20my%20money%20is%20going%20toward%20guilt-free%20spending%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhen%20will%20I%20have%20%24500%2C000%3F%20%241%20million%3F%20When%20will%20I%20be%20able%20to%20retire%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhat%20is%20my%20rich%20life%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20are%20the%20big%2C%20important%20questions%20%E2%80%94%20and%20if%20you%20get%20those%20right%2C%20you%20can%20buy%20as%20many%20coffees%20as%20you%20want%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20your%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sethi.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227c10528a-bb17-43be-9483-889c61433fce%5C%22%3EEliminate%20your%20housing%20payment%20and%20build%20a%20real%20estate%20portfolio%20by%20'house%20hacking'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22jeff%20white%20suleyka%20bolanos%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F694c3492832e0ef1ead6cc60%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDenver-based%20couple%20Jeff%20White%20and%20Suleyka%20Bola%C3%B1os%20retired%20before%2040.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Jeff%20White%20and%20Suleyka%20Bola%C3%B1os%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EReal%20estate%20investing%20is%20an%20effective%20way%20to%20build%20wealth%2C%20but%20the%20barrier%20to%20entry%20can%20be%20intimidating%2C%20especially%20if%20you%20live%20in%20a%20pricey%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20popular%20beginner-friendly%20real%20estate%20strategy%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bhouse%20hacking%26quot%3B%20allows%20investors%20to%20get%20started%20with%20low%20down%20payments%20and%20potentially%20eliminate%20their%20mortgage%20entirely.%20It's%20the%20primary%20strategy%20Jeff%20and%20Suleyka%20Bola%C3%B1os%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-achieve-financial-independence-through-house-hacking-real-estate-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eused%20to%20retire%20before%2040%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20did%20one%20%26quot%3Bhouse%20hack%26quot%3B%20a%20year%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%2C%20they'd%20move%20into%20a%20primary%20residence%20and%20rent%20a%20portion%20of%20it%20(either%20a%20room%20if%20it%20was%20a%20single-family%20home%20or%20a%20unit%20if%20it%20was%20a%20multi-family).%20Their%20first%20house%20hack%20was%20a%20fourplex%2C%20so%20they%20lived%20in%20one%20unit%20and%20rented%20the%20other%20three.%20The%20rental%20income%20covered%20their%20mortgage%20completely%2C%20allowing%20them%20to%20save%20more%20quickly%20for%20their%20next%20house%20hack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20couple%20has%20done%20one%20house%20hack%20a%20year%20for%20eight%20years%2C%20and%20their%20cash%20flow%20has%20increased%20with%20each%20addition%20to%20their%20portfolio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reason%20they%20move%20once%20a%20year%20is%20that%20they%20want%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20owner-occupied%20financing%2C%20which%20typically%20comes%20with%20more%20favorable%20terms%2C%20such%20as%20a%20lower%20down%20payment%20and%20interest%20rate%2C%20compared%20to%20financing%20for%20investment%20properties.%20However%2C%20one%20stipulation%20with%20this%20type%20of%20financing%20is%20that%20you%20have%20to%20live%20in%20the%20property%20for%20at%20least%2012%20months.%20After%20the%20year%20is%20up%2C%20they%20convert%20the%20property%20they%20were%20living%20in%20into%20a%20true%20investment%20property%2C%20buy%20and%20move%20into%20the%20next%20place%2C%20and%20repeat%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20unconventional%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20White.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20just%20buy%20a%20nice%20house%20in%20a%20nice%20neighborhood%2C%20and%20they%20pay%20that%20huge%20mortgage%20payment%20just%20by%20themselves.%20We%20haven't%20had%20a%20mortgage%20payment%20since%202016%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20the%20last%20time%20I%20made%20a%20mortgage%20payment%20without%20having%20renters.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222004b0c9-eed9-4d51-9480-8f5d3810ccee%5C%22%3EBoost%20your%20earnings%20by%20creating%20'one-to-infinity%20leverage'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22rose%20han%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F685edadb85e81483682cf2bf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERose%20Han%20is%20a%20YouTuber%2C%20financial%20educator%2C%20and%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BAdd%20A%20Zero.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Rose%20Han%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGenerally%2C%20the%20more%20income%20streams%20you%20can%20create%2C%20the%20more%20wealth%20you'll%20build%20%E2%80%94%20but%20if%20you're%20going%20to%20have%20just%20one%20income%20stream%2C%20make%20sure%20it's%20leveraged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLeverage%20is%20the%20explanation%20behind%20any%20significant%20wealth%20creation%2C%20no%20matter%20who%20you%20look%20at%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20self-made%20millionaire%20Rose%20Han.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20break%20down%20the%20concept%20of%20leveraged%20income%2C%20Han%20uses%20the%20example%20of%20a%20fitness%20trainer.%20If%20they're%20working%20one-on-one%20with%20a%20client%2C%20that's%20zero%20leverage%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20show%20up%2C%20trade%20hours%20for%20dollars%2C%20and%20you%20get%20paid.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20if%20they%20start%20a%20group%20fitness%20class%20and%20can%20train%20multiple%20clients%20at%20once%2C%20that's%20what%20she%20calls%20%26quot%3Bone-to-many%20leverage%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20their%20earnings%20go%20up%20without%20having%20to%20work%20more%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20final%20level%2C%20%26quot%3Bone-to-infinity%20leverage%2C%26quot%3B%20can%20create%20life-changing%20wealth.%20It%20involves%20doing%20work%20once%20and%20leveraging%20technology%20or%20systems%20to%20reach